article.headline: VMI rolls by Presbyterian 107-93
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Rodney Glasgow scored 26 points and QJ Peterson had 25 points as VMI broke the century mark for the second consecutive game, topping Presbyterian 107-93 Friday. VMI (12-9, 5-3 Big South) opened the game on a 14-4 run, and closed the half on a 12-3 spurt for a 56-41 halftime lead. Presbyterian (4-19, 0-8) cut a big second-half deficit to 90-80 with 5:49 left after a 20-3 run. But Glasgow and Peterson combined to score 14 of the final 17 points for VMI to pull away in the last 5 minutes of the game. The Keydets shot 50 percent from the field and made 15 of 32 3-point attempts. Peterson led VMI with a career-high seven 3-pointers. D.J. Covington added 17 points and 13 rebounds while Brian Brown had 13 points. Reggie Dillard scored 23, Jordan Downing had 22 and Markus Terry had 21 to lead the Blue Hose.
